<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="430" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,633,1452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,633,659]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Nonveiller, G." box="[411,602,633,659]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref3684" refString="Nonveiller, G. (1979 &quot; 1978 &quot;) Recherches sur les Mutillides de l'Afrique (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae). VIII. Revision des genres Ctenotilla, Cephalotilla et Pseudocephalotilla sensu Bischoff. Memoires publies par l'Institut pour la Protection des Plantes, Beograd, 13, 1 - 184. [dating after Lelej &amp; Brothers 2008]" type="journal article" year="1979">Nonveiller 1979</bibRefCitation>
with adding). MALE. Metasomal sterna armed, rarely simple. Head subrectangular. Eyes deeply emarginated on inner margin. Prementum flat. T2 with long lateral felt line, S2 lacking lateral felt line. S7 unarmed, S8 with elongated curved carina laterally, rarely ecarinate. Mandible with strong tooth on inner margin, bidentate apically. Aedeagus with short, lamelliform parapenial lobes. Gonostyle apically narrow, rounded and slightly flattened. FEMALE. Scutellar scale lacking. T2 without pair of pale setae spots, at most with median spot of pale setae. T6 with well-defined glabrous shiny or weakly shagreened pygidial area carinated laterally. T1 without dorsal surface. Head with rounded posterolateral angles. 
<taxonomicName box="[1059,1180,850,876]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma</taxonomicName>
with sides parallel or slightly dilated to propodeum, the latter weakly dilated, wider than the pronotum in dorsal view. Posterior margin of the mesosoma with 7–12 relatively short spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,633,1452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,957,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Sex association.</emphasis>
The male of the 
<typeStatus box="[578,626,958,984]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">type</typeStatus>
species was associated and identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Cameron, 1910" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1910" box="[1088,1436,957,983]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitana">
<emphasis box="[1088,1256,957,983]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Mutilla mitana</emphasis>
Cameron, 1910
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nonveiller, G." box="[186,415,993,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref3684" refString="Nonveiller, G. (1979 &quot; 1978 &quot;) Recherches sur les Mutillides de l'Afrique (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae). VIII. Revision des genres Ctenotilla, Cephalotilla et Pseudocephalotilla sensu Bischoff. Memoires publies par l'Institut pour la Protection des Plantes, Beograd, 13, 1 - 184. [dating after Lelej &amp; Brothers 2008]" type="journal article" year="1979">Nonveiller 1979: 44</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="430" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,633,1452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1029,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Remarks</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nonveiller" authorityYear="1979" box="[431,587,1029,1055]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Strangulotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,587,1029,1055]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Strangulotilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is newly recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[851,912,1029,1055]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">India</collectingCountry>
. In the Oriental Region the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nonveiller" authorityYear="1979" box="[1281,1437,1029,1055]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Strangulotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1281,1437,1029,1055]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Strangulotilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely related to the genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Lelej, 2005" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="2005" box="[466,704,1065,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Lehritilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[466,572,1065,1091]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Lehritilla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." box="[578,704,1065,1092]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" refId="ref3457" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2005) Catalogue of the Mutillidae (Hymenoptera) of the Oriental Region. Vladivostok, Dalnauka, 252 pp." type="book" year="2005">Lelej, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen, 1957" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1957" box="[757,1040,1065,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Zeugomutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[757,906,1065,1091]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Zeugomutilla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, C. - W." box="[912,1040,1065,1092]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" pagination="135 - 224" refId="ref3213" refString="Chen, C. - W. (1957) A revision of the velvety ants or Mutillidae of China (Hymenoptera). Quarterly Journal of the Taiwan Museum, 10 (3 - 4), 135 - 224, 6 pls." type="journal article" year="1957">Chen, 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nonveiller" authorityYear="1979" box="[1202,1358,1065,1091]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Strangulotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1202,1358,1065,1091]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Strangulotilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="2005" box="[370,476,1101,1127]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Lehritilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[370,476,1101,1127]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Lehritilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having: S8 and S7 without any carina or tubercle (in 
<emphasis box="[1143,1256,1101,1127]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="2005" box="[1143,1252,1101,1127]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Lehritilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lehritilla</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
S8 with strong medial carina and S7 with lateral tubercle); gonostylus not bilobed, much longer than volsella, rather straight (in 
<emphasis box="[151,264,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="2005" box="[151,260,1173,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Lehritilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lehritilla</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
gonostylus bilobed with strong basal lobe curved dorsally and narrow short distal lobe); and mandible with strong subbasal inner tooth (in 
<emphasis box="[556,668,1209,1235]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="2005" box="[556,665,1209,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Lehritilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lehritilla</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
mandible bidentate with weak subbasal inner tooth). The females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nonveiller" authorityYear="1979" box="[151,307,1245,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Strangulotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,307,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Strangulotilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1957" box="[580,729,1245,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Zeugomutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[580,729,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Zeugomutilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having: T2 without pale spots located transversely, posterad without (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="2005" box="[255,398,1281,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Strangulotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krombeini">
<emphasis box="[255,398,1281,1308]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">S. krombeini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or with pale band (Afrotropical species) (in 
<emphasis box="[919,1076,1281,1307]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1957" box="[919,1071,1281,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Zeugomutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Zeugomutilla</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
T2 with two pale spots located transversely near the middle) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." box="[492,619,1317,1344]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" refId="ref3457" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2005) Catalogue of the Mutillidae (Hymenoptera) of the Oriental Region. Vladivostok, Dalnauka, 252 pp." type="book" year="2005">Lelej 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,633,1452]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1353,1379]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Natural history</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lelej, 2005" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="2005" box="[395,801,1353,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Strangulotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krombeini">
<emphasis box="[395,669,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Strangulotilla krombeini</emphasis>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3391263301" box="[674,801,1353,1380]" country="Sri Lanka" location="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" specimenCount="24">
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." box="[674,801,1353,1380]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" refId="ref3457" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2005) Catalogue of the Mutillidae (Hymenoptera) of the Oriental Region. Vladivostok, Dalnauka, 252 pp." type="book" year="2005">Lelej, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</materialsCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the Dry Zone of 
<collectingCountry box="[1165,1277,1353,1379]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, mostly at low elevations (
<figureCitation box="[280,346,1389,1415]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1968,1992]" captionTargetBox="[316,1262,248,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-37@2.[295,1293,237,1944]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Map of Sri Lankan Provinces (solid lines), Districts (dashed lines), and the localities, where specimens of Strangulotilla krombeini have been collected (Lelej 2005). District abbreviations follows those of Krombein &amp; Pulawski (1994)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5591647" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5591647/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). A cumulative occurrence per months of 
<specimenCount box="[820,972,1389,1415]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" type="generic">24 specimens</specimenCount>
collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1116,1226,1389,1415]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
during eight years see 
<figureCitation box="[194,262,1425,1451]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1043,1067]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,188,1019]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1019]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Strangulotilla krombeini, cumulative occurrence per months of 24 specimens collected in Sri Lanka during eight non-consecutive years (Lelej 2005)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5591649" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5591649/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Terine &amp; Lelej &amp; Kumar, 2021" authorityName="Terine &amp; Lelej &amp; Kumar" authorityYear="2021" box="[273,544,1425,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Strangulotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sureshani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[273,544,1425,1451]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Strangulotilla sureshani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[551,640,1425,1451]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[551,640,1425,1451]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has been collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[888,946,1425,1451]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">India</collectingCountry>
in the moist deciduous forest.
</paragraph>
